[SN]TITLE[SN]
Juventus 2-1 Fiorentina

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Gonzalo Higuain scored the winner on his Juventus debut as the Italian champions began their Serie A title defence with a win over Fiorentina.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Argentine striker joined the Turin side for £75.3m from Napoli in July and finished from close range in the 75th minute after coming on as a sub.
A header from former Blackburn player Nikola Kalinic had cancelled out Sami Khedira's first-half opener.
Elsewhere, Roma scored four second half goals to hammer Udinese 4-0.
A double from Diego Perotti and late strikes from Edin Dzeko and Mohamed Salah gave them the perfect start to the season.
